<subSubSection id="9ACF684095B66A2014B1102A5903A280" lastPageId="207" lastPageNumber="208" pageId="206" pageNumber="207" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="6CD4550D4B2ADC55660D1D0B9733D888" pageId="206" pageNumber="207">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D122F8A4DD01BAD17373D712CDABA7E8" pageId="206" pageNumber="207">
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="606EF673B06627DA64354B8D78F691EF" captionStart="Figure 183" captionStartId="F183" captionText="Figure 183. Distribution of Conostegia peltata." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure183" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96541" pageId="206" pageNumber="207">183</figureCitation>
). Endemic to Cerro Jefe in Panama, 850-1000 m in elevation.
</paragraph>
<caption id="C98AA07369E425FE64D309A56C3340BE" ID-Zenodo-Dep="974023" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure183" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96541" pageId="206" pageNumber="207" start="Figure 183" startId="F183">
<paragraph id="51D761CFE602E624F1C490D8BAB357C0" pageId="206" pageNumber="207">
<emphasis id="4D53E2D65BA64089A40FD0D6D1D4E085" bold="true" pageId="206" pageNumber="207">Figure 183.</emphasis>
Distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="2BB236F98D1F800605639CB77A07C5FE" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia peltata" order="Myrtales" pageId="206" pageNumber="207" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peltata">
<emphasis id="BE63A6A8CE35F75434AB7CDB249CBE74" italics="true" pageId="206" pageNumber="207">Conostegia peltata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="B7DFA1E96882412D5537D23AE5775A64" pageId="207" pageNumber="208">
<taxonomicName id="D3F2CF1F632A9BC4197BBC17672F12AE" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia peltata" order="Myrtales" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peltata">
<emphasis id="AC8638C63C128F12173C7BB8EC58AF84" italics="true" pageId="207" pageNumber="208">
<pageBreakToken id="E5B9387DB5BC498E9583F700500089D0" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" start="start">Conostegia</pageBreakToken>
peltata
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a Cerro Jefe endemic quite distinctive because of its peltate leaves. It is closely related to another Cerro Jefe endemic, 
<taxonomicName id="27A674096E5E01417AEECEB1B79BCC1B" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia jefensis" order="Myrtales" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jefensis">
<emphasis id="31AF3B5B1B87799A2654D4A9759A8DD8" italics="true" pageId="207" pageNumber="208">Conostegia jefensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as well as to 
<taxonomicName id="DEF1A7E22634BC881547556F9CEBCAB4" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Gleason" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia consimilis" order="Myrtales" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="consimilis">
<emphasis id="2EDCB4CD94A7F0E4BD07EAD539F73920" italics="true" pageId="207" pageNumber="208">Conostegia consimilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="47ADB053A81D8FA1DAED9CD495C030F2" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia trichosantha" order="Myrtales" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trichosantha">
<emphasis id="2DFB22F52E6D3D24E5F5614A7CA19E5D" italics="true" pageId="207" pageNumber="208">Conostegia trichosantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and shares the mostly linear-oblong petals with these species. With these particular petals, this clade is convergent with other taxa in section 
<taxonomicName id="CAE923BF4FE89F982A757F66AFF0862A" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Geniculatae">
<emphasis id="AF0E039DDA988CE9892F390D2019F791" italics="true" pageId="207" pageNumber="208">Geniculatae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
like 
<taxonomicName id="F48A11E03801E8E73087DF1E6E652D9D" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Almeda &amp; Umana" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia friedmaniorum" order="Myrtales" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="friedmaniorum">
<emphasis id="5CA6A046264B4EAC31E8A6D9D4E6255F" italics="true" pageId="207" pageNumber="208">Conostegia friedmaniorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
